[04:47.26]	no less esteemed.
[04:48.76]Varro's Servant	What is a whoremaster, fool?
[04:50.91]Fool	A fool in good clothes, and something like thee.
[04:54.37]	'Tis a spirit: sometime't appears like a lord;
[04:57.63]	sometime like a lawyer; sometime like a philosopher,
[05:01.35]	with two stones moe than's artificial one: he is
[05:04.87]	very often like a knight; and, generally, in all
[05:08.26]	shapes that man goes up and down in from fourscore
[05:11.98]	to thirteen, this spirit walks in.
