[05:20.58]	I have, so much wit thou lackest.
[05:23.06]APEMANTUS	That answer might have become Apemantus.
[05:26.06]All Servants	Aside, aside; here comes Lord Timon.
[05:28.67]	[Re-enter TIMON and FLAVIUS]
[05:29.45]APEMANTUS	Come with me, fool, come.
[05:31.34]Fool	I do not always follow lover, elder brother and
[05:34.80]	woman; sometime the philosopher.
[05:37.21]	[Exeunt APEMANTUS and Fool]
[05:38.00]FLAVIUS	Pray you, walk near: I'll speak with you anon.
[05:41.26]	[Exeunt Servants]
[05:42.04]TIMON	You make me marvel: wherefore ere this time
